value.title: Oregon State's bipedal robot, Cassie, sets Guinness World Record in 100-meter dash
value.excerpt: A bipedal robot named Cassie just set an official Guinness World Record by running 100 meters in 24.73 seconds. With knees that bend like an ostrich's, Cassie is the first bipedal robot to use machine learning to control a running stride on outdoor terrain.

value.title: AI Won’t Replace Human Intuition
value.excerpt: As artificial intelligence (AI) capabilities and applications have expanded, the AI field is fueling fodder for some interesting science-fiction scenarios. Elon Musk, CEO of Tesla—which relies on AI for self-driving and other key functions—has warned the world about “scary outcomes” harnessed by the power of AI-fueled robots akin to those in “Terminator” film series.
